Package: captioner
Type: Package
Title: Numbers Figures and Creates Simple Captions
Version: 2.2.3
Date: 2015-07-15
Authors@R: person("Letaw", "Alathea", email = "alathea@zoology.ubc.ca", role = c("aut", "cre"))
URL: https://github.com/adletaw/captioner
BugReports: https://github.com/adletaw/captioner/issues
Description: Captioner provides a method for automatically numbering figures,
    tables, or other objects.  Captions can be displayed in full, or as citations.
    This is especially useful for adding figures and tables to R markdown
    documents without having to numbering them manually.
License: MIT + file LICENSE
Suggests:
    knitr
VignetteBuilder: knitr
